SIMPLE: sinistrously
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinistrously
<hw>Sin"is*trous*ly</hw> <pr>(s⟦icr⟧n"⟦icr⟧s*tr⟦ucr⟧s*l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a sinistrous manner; perversely;
wrongly; unluckily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With a tendency to use the left hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Many, in their infancy, are <qex>sinistrously</qex> disposed, and
divers continue all their life left-handed.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sink</ent>⟦br⟧
